{"id":1772,"date":"2015-02-24T01:34:21","date_gmt":"2015-02-24T01:34:21","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/twelvershia.net\/?p=1772"},"modified":"2015-08-06T21:38:58","modified_gmt":"2015-08-06T21:38:58","slug":"why-umar-wished-to-cut-the-tongue-of-his-son","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.twelvershia.net\/2015\/02\/24\/why-umar-wished-to-cut-the-tongue-of-his-son\/","title":{"rendered":"Why `Umar wished to cut the tongue of his son?"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/imgstore.org\/a\/67hxw0egsgub?i=1772\" alt=\"\" \/><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Why did `Umar ibn al-Khattab (ra) wish to cut the tongue of his son `Ubaydullah?<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Imami Rafidah claim that `Ali and his four or five companions were always oppressed and humiliated by the Caliphs, those who claim this couldn&#8217;t be more wrong and below we see why.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\nIn Masawi&#8217;-ul-Akhlaq lil-Khara&#8217;iti we read:<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u062d\u064e\u062f\u0651\u064e\u062b\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0631\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e\u0627\u062f\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064f \u0628\u0652\u0646\u064f \u0625\u0650\u0633\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0627\u0642\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0651\u064e\u0644\u064f\u0648\u0644\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064f\u060c \u062b\u0646\u0627 \u0642\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0633\u064c\u060c \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0648\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0644\u064d\u060c \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0647\u0650\u064a\u0651\u0650\u060c \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0639\u064f\u0628\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062f\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u064e \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064e\u060c \u0633\u064e\u0628\u0651\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u0650\u0642\u0652\u062f\u064e\u0627\u062f \u0628\u0652\u0646\u064e \u0639\u064e\u0645\u0652\u0631\u064d\u0648\u060c \u0641\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064f: &#8221; \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0651\u064e \u0646\u064e\u0630\u0652\u0631\u064c \u0625\u0650\u0646\u0652 \u0644\u064e\u0645\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0642\u0652\u0637\u064e\u0639\u0652 \u0644\u0650\u0633\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e\u0647\u064f &#8220;\u060c \u0641\u064e\u0645\u064e\u0634\u064e\u0649 \u0625\u0650\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0646\u064e\u0627\u0633\u064c \u0645\u0650\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0635\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u0650 \u0641\u064e\u0643\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064f\u0648\u0647\u064f\u060c \u0641\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e: &#8221; \u062f\u064e\u0639\u064f\u0648\u0646\u0650\u064a \u0623\u064e\u0642\u0652\u0637\u064e\u0639\u0652 \u0644\u0650\u0633\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e\u0647\u064f\u060c \u0641\u064e\u0644\u0627 \u064a\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0628\u0651\u064e \u0628\u064e\u0639\u0652\u062f\u0650\u064a \u0623\u064e\u0635\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0627\u0628\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0631\u0651\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u0650<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Ahmad bin Mansour al-Ramadi (Thiqah Hafiz) -&gt; Ishaq bin Mansour al-Saluli (Thiqah) -&gt; Qays bin al-Rabi` al-Asadi (Saduq Yukhti&#8217; Shi`ee) -&gt; Wa&#8217;il bin Dawoud al-Taymi (Thiqah) -&gt; `Abdullah bin Yasar al-Bahy (Saduq Yukhti&#8217;)<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">[That `Ubaydullah bin `Umar once cursed at al-Miqdad bin `Amro (al-Aswad), upon hearing this `Umar bin al-Khattab said: &#8220;I vow to cut-off his tongue!&#8221; but a group from the companions of the Prophet (saw) went to `Umar and talked him out of it, so he said: &#8220;Let me cut-off his tongue so that no one may insult the companions of the Messenger (saw) after me.&#8221;]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Also in al-Shifa fi Akhbar al-Mustafa by al-Qadi `Iyad we read:<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0648\u064e\u0631\u064f\u0648\u064a \u0639\u064e\u0646 \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631 \u0628\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u062e\u0637\u0627\u0628: \u0623\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0647 \u0646\u064e\u0630\u064e\u0631 \u0642\u064e\u0637\u0639 \u0644\u0650\u0633\u0627\u0646 \u0639\u064f\u0628\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647 \u0628\u0646 \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631 \u0625\u0630 \u0634\u064e\u062a\u064e\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u0650\u0642\u0652\u062f\u064e\u0627\u062f \u0628\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0623\u0633\u0652\u0648\u062f\u060c \u0641\u064e\u0643\u064f\u0644\u0645 \u0641\u0650\u064a \u0630\u064e\u0644\u0650\u0643\u060c \u0641\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644: \u062f\u064e\u0639\u064f\u0648\u0646\u0650\u064a \u0623\u0642\u0652\u0637\u064e\u0639 \u0644\u0650\u0633\u0627\u0646\u064e\u0647\u060c \u062d\u064e\u062a\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0644\u064e\u0627 \u064a\u064e\u0634\u0652\u062a\u0645 \u0623\u062d\u064e\u062f \u0628\u064e\u0639\u0652\u062f \u0623\u064e\u0635\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0627\u0628 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">[It was narrated from `Umar bin al-Khattab that he vowed to cut-off the tongue of (his son) `Ubaydullah bin `Umar when he cursed at al-Miqdad bin al-Aswad, but they tried talking him out of it so he said: &#8220;Let me cut-off his tongue so that after it no one may insult the companions of the Prophet (saw).&#8221;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<div class=\"mh-excerpt\"><p>Why did `Umar ibn al-Khattab (ra) wish to cut the tongue of his son `Ubaydullah? The Imami Rafidah claim that `Ali and his four or five companions were always oppressed and humiliated by the Caliphs, those who claim this couldn&#8217;t <a class=\"mh-excerpt-more\" href=\"https:\/\/www.twelvershia.net\/2015\/02\/24\/why-umar-wished-to-cut-the-tongue-of-his-son\/\" title=\"Why `Umar wished to cut the tongue of his son?\">[read more]<\/a><\/p>\n<\/div>","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":3894,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[11],"tags":[18],"class_list":{"0":"post-1772","1":"post","2":"type-post","3":"status-publish","4":"format-standard","5":"has-post-thumbnail","7":"category-articles","8":"tag-umar"},"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.twelvershia.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1772","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.twelvershia.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.twelvershia.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.twelvershia.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/2"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.twelvershia.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=1772"}],"version-history":[{"count":1,"href":"https:\/\/www.twelvershia.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1772\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":1773,"href":"https:\/\/www.twelvershia.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1772\/revisions\/1773"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.twelvershia.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/3894"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.twelvershia.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=1772"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.twelvershia.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=1772"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.twelvershia.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=1772"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}